WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.500
Okay, ladies. I'm Beyoncé.
You're backup.

00:02.500 --> 00:06.125
So, back up.

00:06.125 --> 00:07.875
More.

00:07.875 --> 00:08.875
More.

00:08.875 --> 00:10.833
We call it "Mustache TV."
[ Laughs ]

00:10.833 --> 00:12.291
Yeah?
Mm-hmm. Yeah, yeah.

00:12.291 --> 00:14.708
Yeah.
You see, I put
a mustache anywhere I please.

00:14.708 --> 00:16.000
Yep. Any old place.
Uh-huh.

00:16.000 --> 00:18.291
And then we wait for...
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:18.291 --> 00:20.000
[ Laughter ]

00:20.000 --> 00:21.958
She looks like
a little pink Alex Trebek.

00:21.958 --> 00:23.375
I know Trebek.

00:23.375 --> 00:26.000
What is "Do you guys ever
do any work around here?"

00:26.000 --> 00:28.583
Together: Uhh...

00:28.583 --> 00:30.416
So, this branding guy
from the network

00:30.416 --> 00:32.000
is still lurking around, okay?

00:32.000 --> 00:34.083
H-He does not like
when we goof off.

00:34.083 --> 00:36.291
Which is why we make sure
to double down on the goof.

00:36.291 --> 00:37.625
[ Laughs ]

00:37.625 --> 00:39.625
Uh, sorry, we'll get back to
work right away, okay?

00:39.625 --> 00:41.416
Yeah.
Yeah.

00:41.416 --> 00:43.166
[ Laughter ]

00:43.166 --> 00:44.166
[ Laughs sarcastically ]

00:44.166 --> 00:46.000
Peace and bless, fools.

00:46.000 --> 00:47.166
♪ Acting up, drink in my cup ♪

00:47.166 --> 00:48.208
♪ I can care less
what you think ♪

00:48.208 --> 00:49.583
[ As Pache ]
Peace and bless, fools.

00:49.583 --> 00:50.583
Oh, whoa.
[ Gasps ]

00:50.583 --> 00:51.500
That was dead-on.

00:51.500 --> 00:53.208
[ Normal voice ] Yeah?

00:53.208 --> 00:54.416
Well, I'm pretty good
at mimicking voices.
Yeah?

00:54.416 --> 00:56.500
I dated this parrot named Eric,
and he taught me how.

00:56.500 --> 00:58.416
Hey,
do -- do Pache again.

00:58.416 --> 00:59.875
Yeah, yeah. Mas Paches.
Mas Paches.
Come on, come on.

00:59.875 --> 01:01.250
[ As Pache ]
Peace and bless, fools.

01:01.250 --> 01:03.250
[ Laughter ]

01:03.250 --> 01:04.583
♪ I need no permission ♪

01:04.583 --> 01:05.500
♪ Did I mention ♪

01:05.500 --> 01:07.125
♪ Don't pay him any attention ♪

01:07.125 --> 01:09.000
♪ 'Cause you had your turn ♪

01:09.000 --> 01:10.291
♪ And now you're gonna learn ♪

01:10.291 --> 01:12.958
Boy, I really do love
watching Piggy dance.

01:12.958 --> 01:15.083
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪
You know, I've been
so impressed with her lately.

01:15.083 --> 01:16.875
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪
S-She committed herself
to growing as a person...

01:16.875 --> 01:18.708
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪
...and, well,
it really makes her shine.

01:18.708 --> 01:20.750
♪ If you liked it, then you
should have put a ring on it ♪

01:20.750 --> 01:22.416
♪ If you liked it, then you
should have put a ring on it ♪

01:22.416 --> 01:24.458
Although, it could
just be the sweat, uh...

01:24.458 --> 01:26.166
She's really working it.

01:26.166 --> 01:28.000
♪ If you liked it, then you
should have put a ring on it ♪

01:28.000 --> 01:29.750
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

01:29.750 --> 01:31.166
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

01:31.166 --> 01:31.833
[ Crack, thuds ]
Ow!
Bobo: Oh!

01:31.833 --> 01:33.708
Ooh! Oh!
Piggy!

01:33.708 --> 01:35.208
Oh!

01:35.208 --> 01:36.750
Yolanda: Is she all right?
I'm okay, I'm okay.

01:36.750 --> 01:39.458
Janice: Oh, gnarly.
Just gonna walk it off.

01:39.458 --> 01:40.708
[ Crack ]
Whoa!

01:40.708 --> 01:41.500
[ Body thuds ]
Ow!

01:41.500 --> 01:43.375
Oh!

01:43.375 --> 01:45.291
[ Grunts, chuckles ]

01:45.291 --> 01:47.083
Nothing a Band-Aid won't fix!

01:47.083 --> 01:48.958
[ Groaning ]
Okay, come on, come on.

01:48.958 --> 01:50.583
Places!
Places, everybody.

01:50.583 --> 01:51.958
Oh, not good.

01:51.958 --> 01:53.375
Passing out.
Passing out.

01:53.375 --> 01:54.291
[ Body thuds ]

01:54.291 --> 01:56.750
♪♪

01:56.750 --> 01:58.000
[ Ding ]

01:59.708 --> 02:00.875
♪ Ooh! ♪

02:03.583 --> 02:04.500
Yeah!

02:04.500 --> 02:06.250
♪ Unh! ♪

02:06.250 --> 02:08.625
Oh, Kermie!
Aww. It's time to
get things started.

02:12.416 --> 02:14.625
Ha ha ha!

02:14.625 --> 02:17.416
[ Groans ]
Start the music again!

02:17.416 --> 02:19.333
[ All groaning ]
I'm still rehearsing.

02:19.333 --> 02:21.458
Come on!
Let's do this thing!
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

02:21.458 --> 02:22.958
[ Tray clatters ]
Why's everybody
just standing around?

02:22.958 --> 02:23.958
[ Body thuds ]
Kermit: Piggy!

02:23.958 --> 02:25.375
Piggy, Piggy, Piggy,
Piggy.

02:25.375 --> 02:26.833
Listen, you have got to
go to the hospital.
What?

02:26.833 --> 02:27.875
L-Look at your leg. Look down.
No, no, no.

02:27.875 --> 02:29.583
No, I never look down,
Kermit.

02:29.583 --> 02:32.083
Always play to
the back of the theater.

02:32.083 --> 02:33.500
No, no, no, no, no.
D-Deadly! Deadly!

02:33.500 --> 02:34.875
I need some help here!

02:34.875 --> 02:36.291
Uh...Piggy, don't --
don't put weight on that.

02:36.291 --> 02:37.750
Piggy, Piggy.

02:37.750 --> 02:39.708
I've been through injuries
with Piggy before.

02:39.708 --> 02:41.125
For someone who loves attention,

02:41.125 --> 02:44.083
she's weirdly averse
to medical attention.

02:44.083 --> 02:46.250
That's from her days
as a chorus girl.

02:46.250 --> 02:47.833
Check the foot.

02:47.833 --> 02:49.291
Pretty nasty.

02:49.291 --> 02:50.500
Yeah.

02:50.500 --> 02:51.958
[ Gurgles ]
What?

02:51.958 --> 02:52.875
Passing out.

02:52.875 --> 02:53.750
What? No, no, no.
Passing out.

02:53.750 --> 02:55.458
Bobo, no, no, no.
Uh, uh, aah!

02:55.458 --> 02:56.625
Oh, no, look out!
Aah!
[ Body thuds ]

02:56.625 --> 02:58.125
Come along now, Piggy.

02:58.125 --> 02:59.750
The hospital's not so bad.

02:59.750 --> 03:01.416
[ Piggy sighs ]

03:01.416 --> 03:04.208
Uh, they have those
fun, kitschy vending machines.

03:04.208 --> 03:06.708
And I'll bet they have
Bugles corn chips.

03:06.708 --> 03:08.875
Oh, like I don't have
some of <i>those </i>in my purse.

03:08.875 --> 03:10.583
Yeah, you got her, Deadly?
[ Grunting ]

03:10.583 --> 03:11.583
Hey!
Aah! Aah! Aah!

03:11.583 --> 03:12.708
Please. Come on.
Hey, bro.

03:12.708 --> 03:14.208
[ Gasps ]

03:14.208 --> 03:16.583
You corral the pig,
and I'll take over the show.

03:16.583 --> 03:18.250
So what she misses
Willie Nelson tonight?

03:18.250 --> 03:21.250
I got a super-fine deejay chick
who can guest host.

03:21.250 --> 03:22.458
Uncle Deadly:
I have her cornered!

03:22.458 --> 03:24.000
Somebody bring a butterfly net!

03:24.000 --> 03:26.083
No, no, no, Pache.
Definitely please don't do that.

03:26.083 --> 03:27.708
Uh-huh.
Don't -- Don't do anything.

03:27.708 --> 03:29.458
Okay.
I will figure out
how to handle the show, okay?

03:29.458 --> 03:31.958
Right, or I'll just do
what I said before you talked.

03:31.958 --> 03:33.125
But you --

03:33.125 --> 03:35.500
Oh, well, I'll need
this back by Friday.

03:35.500 --> 03:37.458
I'm going to a meadow.

03:37.458 --> 03:38.833
-Hey, guys.
-Hm?

03:38.833 --> 03:39.958
Uh, listen, could you please
keep an eye on Pache

03:39.958 --> 03:41.208
while I take Piggy
to the hospital?

03:41.208 --> 03:42.458
I don't want him
futzing with the show.

03:42.458 --> 03:43.291
-Okay.
-Okeydoke.

03:43.291 --> 03:44.416
Thanks, guys.

03:44.416 --> 03:45.375
Piggy: Hyah!
[ Clattering ]

03:45.375 --> 03:47.416
I got an eye on him
right now.

03:47.416 --> 03:49.833
[ Laughter ]

03:49.833 --> 03:52.458
Piggy:
I don't need a doctor.

03:52.458 --> 03:54.083
[ Grunting ]
Sit down
in the seat here.

03:54.083 --> 03:55.625
Just gonna get you over here.
It will be fine.

03:55.625 --> 03:56.583
Ooh.
It will be fine.

03:56.583 --> 03:58.583
Piggy, look!

03:58.583 --> 04:00.833
Grandma's Cookies.

04:00.833 --> 04:03.000
[ Chuckles ]
You like those.

04:03.000 --> 04:04.708
I hate everything
right now --

04:04.708 --> 04:06.583
cookies, grandmas,
everything.
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

04:06.583 --> 04:08.166
I know, I know.

04:08.166 --> 04:10.708
Oh, I might have
those Fig Newtons, though.

04:10.708 --> 04:12.083
Ah, there you go.

04:12.083 --> 04:13.250
Let me just go get some
change out of the car.

04:13.250 --> 04:14.958
Be right back.
Oh, no, no, no, no.

04:14.958 --> 04:16.708
Come on, Piggy.
That is not going to work.

04:16.708 --> 04:17.875
Ow! Ow, ow.
Now, look, look, look.

04:17.875 --> 04:19.416
Could you just
work with me here?

04:19.416 --> 04:22.208
I'm trying to get you fixed up
and back to the show befo--

04:22.208 --> 04:23.750
Before what?

04:23.750 --> 04:25.583
Before Pache brings in
that deejay to guest host.

04:25.583 --> 04:26.708
Guest host?!
[ Groans ]

04:26.708 --> 04:28.625
Unh-unh. No!
Deadly!

04:28.625 --> 04:29.875
You didn't tell her?!

04:29.875 --> 04:31.166
No, I didn't tell her.

04:31.166 --> 04:33.875
What is your job,
anyway, frog?

04:33.875 --> 04:35.875
Senior VP of
Avoiding and Omitting?

04:35.875 --> 04:38.708
Lies are toxic, Kermit.

04:38.708 --> 04:39.958
Kermit:
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

04:39.958 --> 04:42.958
That's why I live
a 100% transparent life.

04:42.958 --> 04:44.583
No guest host.
No, no.

04:44.583 --> 04:45.750
Piggy. Piggy.
Focus.

04:45.750 --> 04:46.583
Piggy! Piggy!
No, no, no, no, no!

04:46.583 --> 04:48.375
Focus.
No, no, no, no!

04:48.375 --> 04:49.458
Now, come on, Piggy,
will you just -- Piggy!
Focus!

04:49.458 --> 04:54.583
On the encased treats
just waiting to be set free.

04:54.583 --> 04:56.375
Yeah, yeah, do that.

04:56.375 --> 04:57.708
Uh, listen, Deadly.
Just look after her.

04:57.708 --> 04:58.833
Yes.
I-I'm gonna get
you checked in, okay?

04:58.833 --> 05:00.000
Just wait right here.
Here we go.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.166
I'll be right back.
There we are.

05:02.166 --> 05:03.500
[ Clears throat ]

05:03.500 --> 05:04.583
E-Excuse me, sir.
Yeah?

05:04.583 --> 05:05.583
I need to check in
my friend.

05:05.583 --> 05:06.875
Mm.
Uh, hmm?

05:06.875 --> 05:09.416
Piggy asked that you
give her weight in stone

05:09.416 --> 05:11.458
so it's indecipherable.

05:11.458 --> 05:14.000
Deadly, I told you to watch her.
She --

05:14.000 --> 05:16.500
Oh, no. Piggy.
[ Sighs ]

05:16.500 --> 05:19.000
They're coming.
Crank it, grandpa!

05:19.000 --> 05:20.625
You'll never catch me!

05:20.625 --> 05:22.208
See ya, suckers!

05:22.208 --> 05:23.833
Step on it.

05:23.833 --> 05:25.625
[ Wheels squeaking ]

05:25.625 --> 05:27.458
Hey...
Rizzo: Boy, I wish I knew
what he was saying.

05:27.458 --> 05:28.750
Yolanda: Yeah, I know.

05:28.750 --> 05:29.833
Hey, Carl,
can you use them things

05:29.833 --> 05:31.416
on the top of your head?

05:31.416 --> 05:33.375
They look like they should be
able to hear stuff real good.

05:33.375 --> 05:34.583
They're vestigial!

05:34.583 --> 05:36.208
[ All groan ]

05:36.208 --> 05:38.583
We -- We promised Kermit
we would not let Pancho

05:38.583 --> 05:39.958
futz with the show.
Yeah.

05:39.958 --> 05:41.500
Right there --
that's futzing.

05:41.500 --> 05:42.708
-Yeah.
-Yes, it is.

05:42.708 --> 05:44.833
Oh, we got to
get his phone.

05:44.833 --> 05:47.166
Anybody got, like,
an oversized magnet?

05:47.166 --> 05:49.583
'C-'Cause I could hold it,
I could walk by Pache,

05:49.583 --> 05:51.583
and all of his piercings
would come flying out.

05:51.583 --> 05:53.458
That would get his attention.
[ Laughs ]

05:53.458 --> 05:56.458
I'm getting so anxious.
I'm sweating in all of my pits.

05:56.458 --> 05:57.833
-Yeah.
-Yeah, we got to get that phone.

05:57.833 --> 05:59.583
I got this.

05:59.583 --> 06:01.166
Where's he going?
What's he doing?

06:01.166 --> 06:02.333
Uh, excuse me.
Hey!

06:02.333 --> 06:03.333
What --

06:03.333 --> 06:05.208
[ Munching ]

06:05.208 --> 06:07.333
[ Burps ]
Oh.

06:07.333 --> 06:09.583
You know what?
Thank you, fur creature.

06:09.583 --> 06:11.208
I needed an upgrade
anyways.

06:11.208 --> 06:15.250
[ Singsong voice ]
iPhone 7, here I come!

06:15.250 --> 06:16.458
Now what?

06:16.458 --> 06:17.458
-Get him!
-Get him!

06:17.458 --> 06:19.083
[ All shouting ]

06:19.083 --> 06:21.625
Hey, what are you doing?!
What are you -- No!

06:21.625 --> 06:23.250
No!

06:23.250 --> 06:24.833
[ Laughter ]

06:24.833 --> 06:26.750
[ Dance music plays ]
Hey, what --
What is this song?

06:26.750 --> 06:28.125
What is...

06:28.125 --> 06:30.458
Oh, oh, I-I think
he's getting a call!

06:30.458 --> 06:33.250
Hey, hey, hey, turn it up.
I love that song.

06:33.250 --> 06:34.625
♪ Bow-ba-dow-dow ♪

06:34.625 --> 06:35.833
♪ Bow-da-dow-dow ♪

06:35.833 --> 06:37.208
♪ Da-da-dow-dow ♪

06:37.208 --> 06:38.708
Woman: <i>Dr. Davis... </i>

06:38.708 --> 06:41.625
Piggy: Please, stop!
Have you no mercy?!

06:41.625 --> 06:43.125
Okay, I can't
take this anymore.

06:43.125 --> 06:45.166
I-I've got to go
hold her hand or something.

06:45.166 --> 06:47.250
Oh, very well.

06:47.250 --> 06:48.458
Dr. Kilcullen: Stop it.

06:48.458 --> 06:49.625
Piggy?

06:49.625 --> 06:52.208
[ Grunting ]
Give me those lashes!

06:52.208 --> 06:53.750
Mine! Mine!

06:53.750 --> 06:55.250
Miss Piggy!

06:55.250 --> 06:57.250
No one is going to see you,
anyway.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.166
You're not
doing your show tonight.

06:59.166 --> 07:00.458
I have to operate
on that leg,

07:00.458 --> 07:02.208
and you can't wear makeup
during surgery.

07:02.208 --> 07:03.833
Surgery?
No show?

07:03.833 --> 07:06.583
No makeup?!
Oh!

07:06.583 --> 07:07.958
Could we get
a second opinion?

07:11.625 --> 07:13.000
Pache: Hey, Swamp Thing!
Let me out of here!

07:13.000 --> 07:14.000
[ Pounding on door ]
No, Pache!

07:14.000 --> 07:15.500
It's my job to make sure

07:15.500 --> 07:19.166
you stay in there until...

07:19.166 --> 07:20.458
What's the plan again?

07:20.458 --> 07:22.250
-Uh...
-Uh...

07:22.250 --> 07:24.208
Uh, well, you know how
sometimes we do things

07:24.208 --> 07:26.500
without thinking them through,
and they turn out great?

07:26.500 --> 07:28.125
Sweetums: Yeah!

07:28.125 --> 07:29.708
Yeah, we're not sure
this is one of those times.

07:29.708 --> 07:31.375
No.

07:31.375 --> 07:32.416
[ Dance music ringtone plays ]
Uh...
Uh-oh.

07:32.416 --> 07:35.000
Oh, guys, guys, that's
like the fifth call.

07:35.000 --> 07:36.708
If Pache doesn't
answer his phone soon,

07:36.708 --> 07:38.583
people are gonna get
suspicious.

07:38.583 --> 07:40.000
It's ringing again.

07:40.000 --> 07:41.166
-Oh, boy.
-It's ringing again.

07:41.166 --> 07:42.416
Oh, boy.

07:42.416 --> 07:43.583
Wait a minute.

07:43.583 --> 07:45.458
I've got an idea.

07:45.458 --> 07:46.500
Pepe:
Are you in there?

07:46.500 --> 07:48.208
I'm -- I'm still looking!

07:48.208 --> 07:50.375
Geez, it's like an episode
of "Hoarders" in here.

07:50.375 --> 07:51.958
Wait, wait, wait.
Pull me up! Pull me up!

07:51.958 --> 07:53.291
Okay, we're bringing you in.
Bringing you in.

07:53.291 --> 07:54.166
Yolanda: Come on!

07:54.166 --> 07:55.958
Okay.
There we go!

07:55.958 --> 07:57.291
[ Dance music ringtone plays ]
We got him!

07:57.291 --> 07:58.583
[ Laughs ]

07:58.583 --> 08:01.583
[ As Pache ] Yo, yo.
Go for Pache.

08:01.583 --> 08:03.708
It is not a dry heat
in there.

08:03.708 --> 08:05.166
[ Laughs ]

08:05.166 --> 08:08.083
[ Machine beeping ]

08:08.083 --> 08:11.333
Uh, so, I just got off
the phone with the network,

08:11.333 --> 08:14.416
and no matter what I said,
they won't air a rerun.

08:14.416 --> 08:17.166
Oh, so they decided
to go with my idea
of a slide show

08:17.166 --> 08:20.583
of Miss Piggy hairstyles
through the decades, hmm?

08:20.583 --> 08:23.000
Uh, well...

08:23.000 --> 08:24.750
Look, Piggy.

08:24.750 --> 08:26.333
I'm just gonna be
straight with you, okay?

08:26.333 --> 08:28.458
And, uh, you'll probably get
really, really mad

08:28.458 --> 08:31.083
and throw stuff, so I-I'm just
gonna do it from over here.

08:31.083 --> 08:33.166
Um...

08:33.166 --> 08:35.583
they're gonna go ahead and use
Pache's deejay guest host.

08:35.583 --> 08:37.458
This is a nightmare!

08:37.458 --> 08:39.166
Aah!
I-I know, I know.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.166
How come there's no box of
tissues hitting the blinds?

08:43.166 --> 08:45.708
[ Sobs ]

08:45.708 --> 08:47.375
Aw, Piggy.

08:47.375 --> 08:50.083
You know,
i-i-it's only one show.

08:50.083 --> 08:52.208
It's more than that.

08:52.208 --> 08:54.333
Kermie,
I grew up on a farm.

08:54.333 --> 08:55.583
When one of us broke a leg,

08:55.583 --> 08:57.208
they were taken away
and never came back.

08:57.208 --> 08:58.416
Ooh.

08:58.416 --> 08:59.875
My mom would tell me
not to be sad,

08:59.875 --> 09:02.333
that I'd see them again.

09:02.333 --> 09:04.333
And I did.

09:04.333 --> 09:06.958
In the butcher shop window,
at a Cuban barbecue,

09:06.958 --> 09:08.750
in the treat bin
at the pet store.

09:08.750 --> 09:11.166
Oh, Piggy, that --
that's so...

09:11.166 --> 09:13.208
gross.

09:13.208 --> 09:14.708
That must be
really hard for you.

09:14.708 --> 09:17.750
What's happening to me is
the Hollywood version of that.

09:17.750 --> 09:19.875
You come up lame
and miss one show,

09:19.875 --> 09:21.375
and the next thing
you know,

09:21.375 --> 09:23.708
you're signing autographs
next to some guy

09:23.708 --> 09:25.333
who used to play
a 2,000-year-old wizard

09:25.333 --> 09:26.958
but now he's too old.

09:29.208 --> 09:30.750
You know what?

09:30.750 --> 09:32.291
You're doing your show tonight,
and we'll do it from right here.

09:32.291 --> 09:34.125
Really, Kermie?

09:34.125 --> 09:35.375
Yeah!

09:35.375 --> 09:38.083
Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh!
Thank you!

09:38.083 --> 09:40.125
That's everything!

09:40.125 --> 09:42.375
Listen, Piggy, if anybody
can host from a hospital bed,

09:42.375 --> 09:43.208
it's you!

09:43.208 --> 09:44.583
It's gonna be
a great stunt!

09:44.583 --> 09:46.166
Yeah.
Look, I'm gonna go
call the guys

09:46.166 --> 09:47.708
and get the crew over here
to start setting up, okay?

09:47.708 --> 09:48.500
Okay.
Kermit.

09:48.500 --> 09:49.500
All good.

09:49.500 --> 09:51.083
Oh, what's all good?

09:51.083 --> 09:53.416
Deadly, we're shooting the show
from here tonight!

09:53.416 --> 09:55.000
Oh, tremendous!
Yeah.

09:55.000 --> 09:57.583
See, Piggy,
no one's getting hamstrung

09:57.583 --> 09:59.625
just because of
a little old broken bone.

09:59.625 --> 10:00.875
No, they aren't.
[ Chuckles ]

10:00.875 --> 10:02.416
Let's celebrate, shall we?
Mm.

10:02.416 --> 10:04.458
I'll ring
for some champagne.

10:04.458 --> 10:06.875
Whoa!
Oh!

10:06.875 --> 10:08.875
Can we get a nurse
in here?!

10:08.875 --> 10:11.500
[ Screaming ]
Or someone familiar
with charcuterie.

10:11.500 --> 10:13.708
It's happening!

10:15.708 --> 10:18.250
Sweetums: Well, since you're
waiting, I made you some snacks.

10:18.250 --> 10:21.125
Ants on a log?

10:21.125 --> 10:23.708
They're yummy.

10:23.708 --> 10:25.708
Good boy.

10:27.125 --> 10:28.458
Go on.

10:28.458 --> 10:30.833
So, we've got some time.

10:30.833 --> 10:33.708
Um, why don't you
tell me about yourself?

10:33.708 --> 10:35.166
What were you like
as a kid?

10:35.166 --> 10:36.875
Friggin' awesome.

10:38.333 --> 10:39.750
Chubby.

10:39.750 --> 10:44.375
Believe it or not,
I used to be big, too.

10:44.375 --> 10:45.583
[ As Pache ]
You're welcome.

10:45.583 --> 10:47.000
Peace and bless.

10:47.000 --> 10:49.833
[ Laughter ]

10:49.833 --> 10:52.250
[ Normal voice ]
Guys, that was Pepsi.

10:52.250 --> 10:54.625
I just changed the color of
every Pepsi can in the world

10:54.625 --> 10:56.166
to match my hair clip.

10:56.166 --> 10:57.958
[ Laughter ]

10:57.958 --> 10:59.583
With the cellphone,
we have a lot of power.

10:59.583 --> 11:01.083
Oh, yeah.

11:01.083 --> 11:03.583
Now I'm making him propose
to three girls,

11:03.583 --> 11:07.125
including "Heather, Blonde from
Kansas or Something."

11:07.125 --> 11:08.375
[ Laughter ]

11:08.375 --> 11:09.500
[ Dance music ringtone plays ]

11:09.500 --> 11:10.625
Who's that?
It's Kermit.

11:10.625 --> 11:12.708
Answer it, answer it.

11:12.708 --> 11:16.000
[ As Pache ] What it do, shorty?
It's Pache.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.625
[ Chuckles ]
Kermit: Hey, Pache, we're gonna
do the show from the hospital,

11:18.625 --> 11:20.958
so you can just cancel
the deejay.

11:20.958 --> 11:23.583
Dope.
Your staff is bomb, b-t-dubs.

11:23.583 --> 11:25.708
They all deserve raises.
Oh!

11:25.708 --> 11:27.458
And I started some new
hair-loss meds

11:27.458 --> 11:29.208
that are making me
hallucinate,

11:29.208 --> 11:32.208
so if I tell you
I was held against my will,

11:32.208 --> 11:33.875
don't believe me.

11:33.875 --> 11:35.208
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

11:35.208 --> 11:36.583
Bye.

11:36.583 --> 11:38.166
Oh, boy.

11:38.166 --> 11:40.750
[ Laughter ]

11:41.500 --> 11:42.875
Ugh.

11:42.875 --> 11:44.208
These are
the extra long ones, right?

11:44.208 --> 11:45.416
Yes, dear.
Okay.

11:45.416 --> 11:46.708
Okay, see you in 10.

11:46.708 --> 11:49.875
Oh, good!
Rowlf, you're here!

11:49.875 --> 11:51.500
Oh, I am so happy
you agreed to come!

11:51.500 --> 11:53.375
Well, no one was
more surprised than me to hear

11:53.375 --> 11:55.166
that you wanted to do
one of our old sketches

11:55.166 --> 11:56.500
on tonight's show.
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

11:56.500 --> 11:57.458
Uh, where's
hair and makeup?

11:57.458 --> 12:00.000
Oh, it's like
here and here.

12:00.000 --> 12:01.125
[ Laughs ]

12:01.125 --> 12:02.125
Oh.
Good to be back.

12:02.125 --> 12:03.125
Yeah.
And I can, like,

12:03.125 --> 12:04.333
wander around the hospital

12:04.333 --> 12:06.958
and curl up next to
patients nearing death

12:06.958 --> 12:08.333
like that psychic cat.

12:08.333 --> 12:10.291
O...kay.

12:10.291 --> 12:13.125
All right, I got everything here
we need to manage the segment.

12:13.125 --> 12:15.458
Oh, and Fozzie's all set up
back at the studio.

12:15.458 --> 12:17.250
Oh, good.
You know something, Scooter?

12:17.250 --> 12:18.750
I think this is really
gonna be a great show.

12:18.750 --> 12:20.500
Wait a minute.
I'm getting feedback.

12:20.500 --> 12:22.750
Man, Piggy's monitor
is making a lot of noise.

12:22.750 --> 12:24.166
Huh.
Oh, I'll call the nurse.

12:24.166 --> 12:25.458
I think it's this one.

12:25.458 --> 12:27.583
Wait, Piggy, no, no, no.
That's not the call button.

12:27.583 --> 12:29.083
Yes, it is.
We're on in 5,

12:29.083 --> 12:30.875
4, 3...
No, that's
your morphine drip!

12:30.875 --> 12:33.250
...2...
Uh-oh.

12:33.250 --> 12:38.500
And now, here's Miss Piggy!

12:38.500 --> 12:41.000
[ Cheers and applause ]

12:41.000 --> 12:42.833
Hello, hello!

12:42.833 --> 12:44.083
Hello, America!

12:44.083 --> 12:45.458
You're not dreaming.

12:45.458 --> 12:47.416
You <i>are </i>in bed with me!

12:47.416 --> 12:49.416
[ Laughter ]

12:49.416 --> 12:52.458
Tonight is going to be
a very special show,

12:52.458 --> 12:54.375
because earlier today,

12:54.375 --> 12:58.416
I broke my leg
in a heroic dancing accident.

12:58.416 --> 13:00.833
But I am a trouper,

13:00.833 --> 13:04.375
and King Tut and
Jolly Green Giant, am I right?

13:04.375 --> 13:05.958
[ Laughs ]

13:05.958 --> 13:07.458
Whee!

13:07.458 --> 13:08.875
Why is Piggy
talking like my aunt

13:08.875 --> 13:10.708
who lives in
a pay-by-the-hour motel?!

13:10.708 --> 13:13.333
Cut to Fozzie.
I'm gonna get that clicker.

13:13.333 --> 13:16.083
[ Laughter ]
Up next, I'm being told...

13:16.083 --> 13:17.333
Stretch.

13:17.333 --> 13:19.458
...this.

13:19.458 --> 13:20.458
[ Laughter ]

13:20.458 --> 13:22.500
And this.

13:22.500 --> 13:23.500
[ Laughter ]

13:23.500 --> 13:24.583
[ Grunting ]

13:24.583 --> 13:26.000
I'm painting my face

13:26.000 --> 13:29.500
and it feels amazing,
Captain Unicorn!

13:29.500 --> 13:31.125
Let go of the morphine!

13:31.125 --> 13:31.958
Ooh!
[ Clatter ]

13:31.958 --> 13:32.708
Ohh.

13:35.958 --> 13:37.000
[ Laughs ]
Pache just bought

13:37.000 --> 13:38.250
the office
flowers of the month club.

13:38.250 --> 13:40.583
[ Gasps ] Ooh, if we get
snapdragons, I call dibs.

13:40.583 --> 13:41.875
They look like my face.
Look.

13:45.250 --> 13:46.583
You see it?

13:46.583 --> 13:47.708
I'm gonna keep doing this
till you see it.

13:47.708 --> 13:49.000
Here, watch. Ahhhhh.

13:49.000 --> 13:51.125
Stop it.

13:51.125 --> 13:52.375
Stop it.

13:52.375 --> 13:54.458
I'm a snapdragon. Roar.
You're not.

13:54.458 --> 13:57.083
Hey, hey, hey,
bad news, guys.
What?

13:57.083 --> 13:59.625
I just got off the phone
with my cousin who's a cop.

13:59.625 --> 14:02.083
He says that what we're doing
could be considered kidnapping.

14:02.083 --> 14:03.500
I think we've got to
let Pache go.

14:03.500 --> 14:04.833
No, no, no, no.

14:04.833 --> 14:06.583
If we let him go,
he will tell everyone,

14:06.583 --> 14:08.333
and we'll all get fired.
Yeah.

14:08.333 --> 14:11.000
No, wait, wait.
Maybe Pache won't say anything.

14:11.000 --> 14:13.000
He's not such a bad guy.

14:13.000 --> 14:13.750
-What?
-What are you talking about?

14:13.750 --> 14:16.333
Pache: Let me out of here
right now!

14:16.333 --> 14:19.583
Look, he just had
a really difficult relationship

14:19.583 --> 14:21.416
with his father.

14:21.416 --> 14:24.250
He never told Pache
"I love you."

14:24.250 --> 14:25.583
Hmm?

14:25.583 --> 14:27.708
No wonder they haven't talked
in years.

14:27.708 --> 14:29.583
-Wow.
-Wow.

14:29.583 --> 14:31.000
Oh, yeah.
We went there.

14:31.000 --> 14:32.500
Hm.

14:32.500 --> 14:36.125
Well, if Pancho and his poppy
don't talk anymore...

14:36.125 --> 14:37.250
Yeah?

14:37.250 --> 14:39.291
...that might work
to our advantage, okay?

14:39.291 --> 14:40.166
-Oh.
-Ooh.

14:40.166 --> 14:41.708
I think I have an idea.

14:41.708 --> 14:42.583
[ Laughs ]

14:42.583 --> 14:44.833
I've got
lots of ideas!

14:44.833 --> 14:46.166
For this situation?

14:46.166 --> 14:47.416
Oh.

14:47.416 --> 14:48.875
Nah.

14:48.875 --> 14:50.291
For "Shark Tank."

14:50.291 --> 14:52.833
[ Cheers and applause ]

14:52.833 --> 14:54.625
♪ Burr be dicke burr ♪

14:54.625 --> 14:56.083
♪ Burr dicke bum ♪

14:56.083 --> 14:57.875
♪ Burr dicke dee ♪

14:57.875 --> 15:00.583
♪ Vurm be dinke
vurm dicke vurr ♪

15:00.583 --> 15:01.875
♪ Bork, bork, bork ♪
♪ Bork, bork, bork ♪

15:01.875 --> 15:03.500
[ Laughs ]
[ Meeping ]

15:03.500 --> 15:05.250
Here at "Up Late,"
the Swedish Chef

15:05.250 --> 15:07.583
and Dr. Bunsen Honeydew
have been experimenting

15:07.583 --> 15:11.125
with something new called
molecular gastronomy.

15:11.125 --> 15:11.875
Hmm.

15:11.875 --> 15:13.583
De vurde freezy.

15:13.583 --> 15:15.166
De vurde foamin.

15:15.166 --> 15:17.458
Now, molecular gastronomy
investigates

15:17.458 --> 15:19.625
the physical and chemical
transformations

15:19.625 --> 15:21.708
that occur in cooking.

15:21.708 --> 15:24.291
Mm.
De vurde fursty muu-muu-buu.

15:24.291 --> 15:25.500
Muu-muu-buu.
Exactly.

15:25.500 --> 15:26.458
[ Laughter ]
Whoo!

15:26.458 --> 15:28.333
I'm making
meatball ice cream

15:28.333 --> 15:32.083
by using liquid nitrogen
to flash-freeze the meatball.

15:32.083 --> 15:34.833
I'm speeding up the process
by adding three times

15:34.833 --> 15:37.000
the usual amount
of volatile chemicals.

15:37.000 --> 15:38.250
[ Audience "Oohs" ]

15:38.250 --> 15:39.083
Mm.

15:39.083 --> 15:40.166
Ooh.

15:40.166 --> 15:42.333
Okay, that's weird.

15:42.333 --> 15:44.708
All right, Beakey.
Here we go.

15:44.708 --> 15:46.583
[ Panicking ]
Open wide!

15:46.583 --> 15:48.583
[ Laughter ]
There.

15:48.583 --> 15:50.125
[ Trembling ]

15:50.125 --> 15:52.125
Whoa-a-a-a-a!

15:52.125 --> 15:54.208
[ Audience gasps ]

15:54.208 --> 15:55.958
Well, this is why
I don't eat solids anymore.

15:55.958 --> 15:58.416
Speaking of which,
I brought a pork chop.

15:58.416 --> 16:00.333
Oh. [ Laughs ]

16:00.333 --> 16:02.708
Let's check in with Miss Piggy.
[ Applause ]

16:02.708 --> 16:05.125
Thank you, Fizzie.

16:05.125 --> 16:09.833
And next, this favorite sketch
been done hasn't time so long.

16:09.833 --> 16:10.958
[ Laughter ]

16:10.958 --> 16:12.500
Scooter: Cut to Deadly.

16:12.500 --> 16:18.250
And now, the long-awaited return
of "Veterinarian's Hospital,"

16:18.250 --> 16:23.375
the continuing story of a quack
who's gone to the dogs.

16:23.375 --> 16:24.833
Me!
Oh, my God.

16:24.833 --> 16:26.583
[ Humming ]
What are you doing?

16:26.583 --> 16:28.250
Oh, don't worry.
I won't bite.
Aah!

16:28.250 --> 16:30.458
Unless you come at me
with a rolled-up newspaper.

16:30.458 --> 16:32.583
[ Laughter ]

16:32.583 --> 16:34.250
Just here
to check your reflexes!

16:34.250 --> 16:35.458
Oh, hell no,
not with that thing!

16:35.458 --> 16:37.125
Reflexes seem fine!

16:37.125 --> 16:38.458
[ Laughter ]

16:38.458 --> 16:40.458
Hey, Nurse, that's not
the right instrument.

16:40.458 --> 16:42.000
Well, what is
the right instrument?

16:42.000 --> 16:44.166
This is
the right instrument.

16:44.166 --> 16:45.375
[ Humming ]
What's happening?

16:45.375 --> 16:46.583
Someone help!
I need help!

16:46.583 --> 16:47.958
[ Humming ]

16:47.958 --> 16:49.875
Hey, Kermit,
we're trending on Twitter.

16:49.875 --> 16:51.375
People are loving
the show.

16:51.375 --> 16:54.416
#rowlfisback.
#piginahospitalblanket.

16:54.416 --> 16:56.833
Wow, Scooter.
This is really working.

16:56.833 --> 16:57.583
Mm-hmm.

16:59.583 --> 17:01.708
And now a man kind enough
to visit

17:01.708 --> 17:04.250
even though they wouldn't
validate his parking.

17:04.250 --> 17:07.416
Please welcome
Mr. Willie Nelson!

17:07.416 --> 17:09.750
[ Cheers and applause ]

17:09.750 --> 17:11.166
Hi, Piggy.

17:11.166 --> 17:13.458
Looks like you could use
a little cheering up, darling.

17:13.458 --> 17:15.958
[ Chuckling ] Now, Willie, I
think we're both happy enough.

17:15.958 --> 17:17.333
[ Laughter ]
But I'd love a song.

17:17.333 --> 17:18.625
You got it.

17:18.625 --> 17:21.958
[ Willie Nelson's
"On the Road Again" plays ]

17:24.583 --> 17:27.625
♪ On the road again ♪

17:27.625 --> 17:32.083
♪ Just can't wait
to get on the road again ♪

17:32.083 --> 17:35.708
♪ The life I love is
makin' music with my friends ♪

17:35.708 --> 17:38.250
♪ And I can't wait
to get on the road again ♪

17:39.708 --> 17:43.083
♪ On the road again ♪

17:43.083 --> 17:45.708
♪ Goin' places
that I've never been ♪

17:45.708 --> 17:47.250
Yeah!

17:47.250 --> 17:51.125
♪ Seein' things
that I may never see again ♪

17:51.125 --> 17:53.583
♪ I can't wait
to get on the road again ♪

17:54.708 --> 17:57.208
♪ On the road again ♪

17:57.208 --> 18:00.458
♪ Like a band of gypsies,
we go down the highway ♪

18:01.500 --> 18:03.958
♪ We're the best of friends ♪

18:03.958 --> 18:08.083
♪ Insisting that the world
keep turning our way ♪

18:08.083 --> 18:09.708
♪ And our way ♪

18:09.708 --> 18:11.083
♪ Is on the road again ♪

18:11.083 --> 18:13.166
Yeah.

18:13.166 --> 18:15.875
♪ Just can't wait
to get on the road again ♪

18:15.875 --> 18:17.708
We're right behind you,
Willie!

18:17.708 --> 18:21.125
♪ The life I love is
makin' music with my friends ♪

18:21.125 --> 18:24.458
♪ And I can't wait to get
on the road again ♪

18:24.458 --> 18:25.875
Yeah!

18:25.875 --> 18:28.125
[ Cheers and applause ]
Willie! Willie!

18:28.125 --> 18:30.875
Ladies and gentlemen,
Nillie Welson!

18:30.875 --> 18:32.375
Aah!

18:32.375 --> 18:33.208
[ Body thuds ]

18:33.208 --> 18:35.291
[ Gasps ]

18:35.291 --> 18:38.000
[ Coughs ]

18:38.000 --> 18:41.500
Okay, okay, okay. We have
decided to set you free, Pancho.

18:41.500 --> 18:43.416
Ah, ba-ba-ba,
jub-jub-jub-jub!

18:43.416 --> 18:45.458
Before you try to
put us in the jails,

18:45.458 --> 18:46.458
somebody
wants to talk to you.

18:46.458 --> 18:48.083
Yeah.

18:48.083 --> 18:51.291
[ As Pache ] Oh, man, that's
so good to hear, Daddy-o.

18:51.291 --> 18:53.083
What is happening?

18:53.083 --> 18:54.166
It's your dad!

18:54.166 --> 18:55.875
Yeah.

18:58.708 --> 19:01.625
Papa?

19:01.625 --> 19:04.333
[ Gasps ]
I love you, too, Papa.

19:04.333 --> 19:07.208
Well, I don't know
why we never said it earlier.

19:07.208 --> 19:09.458
I mean, you're the adult,
so I was just -- Yes, sir.

19:09.458 --> 19:10.458
Yes, sir.

19:10.458 --> 19:11.583
Okay.

19:11.583 --> 19:12.875
I'll see you soon.

19:12.875 --> 19:15.208
I don't know what to say.

19:15.208 --> 19:17.000
My papa, he wants me
to go home

19:17.000 --> 19:19.583
and run the family
sporting-goods business.

19:19.583 --> 19:21.833
Wow!
That's -- Oh!

19:21.833 --> 19:25.833
Which is really
everything I ever wanted.

19:25.833 --> 19:26.875
Aw.

19:26.875 --> 19:29.250
I know, brother.
I know.

19:29.250 --> 19:30.458
[ Laughs ]

19:30.458 --> 19:32.416
Oh.
I got to go home.

19:32.416 --> 19:34.583
[ Normal voice ] Wow, gee.
How long you gonna be gone for?

19:34.583 --> 19:35.708
Yeah.

19:35.708 --> 19:37.458
[ Sighs ]
As long as it takes.

19:37.458 --> 19:39.416
Oh, that's great!

19:39.416 --> 19:41.166
That's wonderful
family values.
For you.
I mean, it's wonderful.

19:41.166 --> 19:43.583
Thank you, creatures,
for this priceless gift.

19:43.583 --> 19:44.333
Oh.
You're welcome.

19:44.333 --> 19:45.708
Peace and bless.

19:45.708 --> 19:47.250
Peace and bless.
Yeah, yeah.

19:47.250 --> 19:49.000
Huh.

19:50.875 --> 19:52.000
[ Dance music ringtone plays ]

19:52.000 --> 19:54.208
-Ah!
-Whoo!

19:54.208 --> 19:56.416
[ Laughs ]

19:56.416 --> 19:58.166
-Yeah!
-Whoo-hoo!

19:58.166 --> 19:59.500
[ Roars ]
Oh, no, no, no!

19:59.500 --> 20:01.333
[ Munching ]

20:01.333 --> 20:03.458
Kermit?
Yeah?

20:03.458 --> 20:06.625
I can't thank you enough for
making all this happen tonight.

20:06.625 --> 20:09.083
Aww. Well, I just
made some calls, Piggy.

20:09.083 --> 20:09.875
<i>You </i>made it happen.

20:09.875 --> 20:11.291
Aw.
Mm-hmm.

20:11.291 --> 20:13.833
Miss Piggy, we're ready
to get you into surgery.

20:13.833 --> 20:15.333
[ Groans ]
But first,

20:15.333 --> 20:17.500
I need verbal confirmation
that you understand

20:17.500 --> 20:19.291
the risks
of general anesthesia.

20:19.291 --> 20:21.458
I understand.

20:21.458 --> 20:22.833
Just in case, though...

20:22.833 --> 20:23.500
Mm-hmm.

20:23.500 --> 20:25.000
...I love you, Kermit.

20:25.000 --> 20:28.333
Oh, I-I-I love you, too,
Piggy.

20:28.333 --> 20:29.750
Did you hear that?

20:29.750 --> 20:31.083
Yolanda: Did he just say
"I love you"?

20:31.083 --> 20:32.458
Bobo: Hey, guys.
That camera's still on.

20:32.458 --> 20:34.458
And just in case,

20:34.458 --> 20:38.625
I love you, hand sanitizer
dispenser thingy.

20:38.625 --> 20:42.583
And you, too, Space Cowboy
and Giant Talking Giraffe.

20:44.333 --> 20:45.583
I love her.

20:45.583 --> 20:48.500
[ All gasping ]

20:54.083 --> 20:56.875
♪ And I patched up
your broken wing ♪

21:01.416 --> 21:04.083
♪ And hung around a while ♪

21:09.000 --> 21:10.708
♪ Trying to keep
your spirits up ♪

21:16.375 --> 21:18.750
♪ And your fever down ♪

21:18.750 --> 21:19.708
Whoa!

21:19.708 --> 21:20.958
[ Body thuds ]

21:20.958 --> 21:21.708
Ow.
